without bothering anybody,

267
00:14:39,829 --> 00:14:41,913
we'll let you have
whichever you want.

268
00:14:41,948 --> 00:14:43,031
( laughing )

269
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:45,917
Ah, well, if you'll
all excuse me.

270
00:14:47,754 --> 00:14:50,788
Come on, I'll introduce you.

271
00:14:50,790 --> 00:14:54,175
Pima Ryan, this is our
art director Stan Rizzo.

272
00:14:55,462 --> 00:14:57,462
So you'll be cutting up
my work, will you?

273
00:14:58,631 --> 00:15:00,715
Well, I try
to treat it like art

274
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:02,967
even though it's just
selling something.

275
00:15:02,969 --> 00:15:05,186
All art is selling something.

276
00:15:05,221 --> 00:15:08,106
No, we're actually
selling something.

277
00:15:08,141 --> 00:15:09,807
Today it's vermouth.

278
00:15:09,809 --> 00:15:12,060
I apologize the models
have so many teeth.

279
00:15:12,112 --> 00:15:13,945
I know you're not used to that.

280
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:15,980
Pleasure to meet you.

281
00:15:19,486 --> 00:15:20,952
I'm sorry about that.

282
00:15:20,987 --> 00:15:24,455
He has a hard time
with... new people.

283
00:15:24,491 --> 00:15:26,958
- No, he hates himself.
- ( laughs )

284
00:15:26,993 --> 00:15:29,627
I don't think so.
He's got a huge ego.

285
00:15:29,662 --> 00:15:32,163
And he's a photographer.

286
00:15:32,215 --> 00:15:35,166
Ah, men like him
don't bother me.

287
00:15:35,168 --> 00:15:37,001
And they shouldn't
bother you either.

288
00:15:37,053 --> 00:15:38,719
Look at all you're doing here.

289
00:15:38,755 --> 00:15:40,755
Just my job.

290
00:15:42,725 --> 00:15:44,258
Good morning, girls.

291
00:15:44,310 --> 00:15:46,344
Could you take your places?

292
00:15:58,108 --> 00:16:00,658
- Good morning.
- It's 11:30.

293
00:16:00,693 --> 00:16:02,493
Where were you?
I was worried.

294
00:16:02,529 --> 00:16:05,246
- I was sleepy.
- Mr. Sterling's in there.

295
00:16:05,281 --> 00:16:07,031
He's not to be disturbed.

296
00:16:10,787 --> 00:16:12,286
Who are you hiding from?

297
00:16:12,338 --> 00:16:15,089
Got two secretaries
and three telephones.

298
00:16:15,125 --> 00:16:17,875
I feel like Marlin Perkins
is chasing me on the savannah.

299
00:16:17,927 --> 00:16:20,428
- Hiding is pointless.
- I've got work to do.

300
00:16:20,463 --> 00:16:22,213
That's the other
reason I'm here.

301
00:16:22,215 --> 00:16:24,348
McCann represents Derby Foods.

302
00:16:24,384 --> 00:16:25,766
Peter Pan Peanut Butter.

303
00:16:25,802 --> 00:16:27,935
- They're making a cookie.
- Sounds delicious.

304
00:16:27,971 --> 00:16:29,804
McCann also represents Nabisco.

305
00:16:29,856 --> 00:16:31,556
National Biscuit Company.

306
00:16:31,608 --> 00:16:33,391
They got the word cookie
in their name.

307
00:16:33,443 --> 00:16:36,027
No, they don't.
Do we have a shot at Derby?

308
00:16:36,062 --> 00:16:37,528
No, it's just a cookie.

309
00:16:37,564 --> 00:16:39,564
McCann's clients are our clients.
We're helping out.

310
00:16:39,566 --> 00:16:41,566
You and Peter are taking them
golfing tomorrow.

311
00:16:41,568 --> 00:16:43,484
- I can't make it.
- <i> ( intercom buzzes )</i>

312
00:16:43,536 --> 00:16:46,120
Meredith: <i>There's a messenger
here from your attorney's office.</i>

313
00:16:46,156 --> 00:16:48,456
<i>He needs your signature.</i>

314
00:16:48,491 --> 00:16:50,208
So why can't you go golfing?

315
00:16:50,243 --> 00:16:52,827
Since Burt Peterson's
the account man.

316
00:16:58,468 --> 00:16:59,884
Good news or bad news?

317
00:16:59,919 --> 00:17:02,720
Good news.
It's almost over.

318
00:17:02,755 --> 00:17:06,174
Well, don't settle until
you get the number you want.

319
00:17:06,226 --> 00:17:07,675
Take it from me,
no matter what she says,

320
00:17:07,727 --> 00:17:09,227
you have given her
the good life.

321
00:17:09,262 --> 00:17:10,928
She would never have had it.

322
00:17:10,980 --> 00:17:12,430
Megan is not Jane.

323
00:17:12,482 --> 00:17:15,850
So she never said you squandered
her youth and beauty?

324
00:17:15,902 --> 00:17:17,435
Used up her childbearing years?

325
00:17:17,437 --> 00:17:19,153
Thwarted her career?
What career?

326
00:17:19,189 --> 00:17:20,821
- She's a consumer.
- <i> ( intercom buzzes )</i>

327
00:17:20,857 --> 00:17:22,940
Meredith: <i>Mr. Sterling,
are you still at lunch?</i>

328
00:17:22,942 --> 00:17:24,442
<i>They're wondering.</i>

329
00:17:24,444 --> 00:17:25,776
She made her choices.

330
00:17:27,914 --> 00:17:30,531
<i>( door opens, closes )</i>

331
00:17:34,326 --> 00:17:37,327
[ <i>"Golddigger" playing</i> ]

332
00:17:37,362 --> 00:17:39,830
You're very good.

333
00:17:39,865 --> 00:17:41,832
( sighs )

334
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:43,533
Can I help you?

335
00:17:43,585 --> 00:17:47,003
Well, I've been told that my
negatives belong to the agency

336
00:17:47,039 --> 00:17:49,706
and therefore processing
has to be done at your lab.

337
00:17:49,758 --> 00:17:51,675
I'm not comfortable with that.

338
00:17:51,710 --> 00:17:54,211
I hate to break it to you,

339
00:17:54,213 --> 00:17:56,012
but it's not really
yours anymore.

340
00:17:57,299 --> 00:17:58,932
Don't you have a darkroom here?

341
00:17:58,967 --> 00:18:01,434
Yes, but I can't do that.

342
00:18:03,388 --> 00:18:05,305
I started off as a clerk

343
00:18:05,357 --> 00:18:08,108
with a newspaper in Sarasota.

344
00:18:08,143 --> 00:18:10,527
All I wanted was to get
in that darkroom.

345
00:18:10,562 --> 00:18:14,614
It's a nice thing to have,
especially in the city.

346
00:18:14,650 --> 00:18:18,068
So, you're a photographer.

347
00:18:19,238 --> 00:18:21,371
I do everything.

348
00:18:21,406 --> 00:18:23,039
I'm an art director.

349
00:18:23,075 --> 00:18:26,042
You must show me your work.

350
00:18:26,078 --> 00:18:28,211
I don't know.

351
00:18:29,915 --> 00:18:33,383
I can feel the tension
of your need for my opinion.

352
00:18:33,418 --> 00:18:36,586
( scoffs )

353
00:18:36,638 --> 00:18:39,422
I wouldn't mind
you taking a look

354
00:18:39,424 --> 00:18:41,841
if you promise to be honest.

355
00:18:41,894 --> 00:18:44,177
Let's see how brave you are.

356
00:18:49,318 --> 00:18:51,268
Hello?

357
00:18:51,270 --> 00:18:53,603
Mother?
Marie-France?

358
00:18:53,655 --> 00:18:55,438
<i>Bonjour.</i>

359
00:18:55,882 --> 00:18:57,263
_

360
00:18:57,591 --> 00:18:58,643
_

