00:19:12,557 --> 00:19:13,720
_

371
00:19:14,126 --> 00:19:15,125
Thank you.

372
00:19:15,613 --> 00:19:16,871
_

373
00:19:16,929 --> 00:19:19,273
For you to enjoy
and for him to pay for.

374
00:19:19,274 --> 00:19:21,093
I'm not changing rooms.

375
00:19:21,094 --> 00:19:22,358
Well, she's made plans for us.

376
00:19:22,359 --> 00:19:24,400
_

377
00:19:24,410 --> 00:19:26,836
_

378
00:19:26,837 --> 00:19:28,620
Absolutely not.
This isn't a vacation.

379
00:19:28,672 --> 00:19:29,787
( sighs )

380
00:19:29,788 --> 00:19:30,857
_

381
00:19:30,858 --> 00:19:35,387
_

382
00:19:36,129 --> 00:19:37,929
We'll have a contest.

383
00:19:37,964 --> 00:19:40,715
We'll see if we can get
drunker than Maman.

384
00:19:40,767 --> 00:19:42,884
( laughs )

385
00:19:44,499 --> 00:19:47,348
_

386
00:19:50,310 --> 00:19:53,144
- Doorman:<i> Evening, Doctor.</i>
- Arnold:<i> Can you hold that?</i>

387
00:19:56,533 --> 00:19:58,950
Oh, hello, Don.

388
00:19:58,985 --> 00:20:00,735
Hello, Arnold.

389
00:20:05,709 --> 00:20:08,326
- Good evening.
- This is Diana.

390
00:20:08,328 --> 00:20:10,662
- Arnold and Sylvia.
- Hello.

391
00:20:12,048 --> 00:20:14,465
Brought the whole
restaurant home, did you?

392
00:20:14,501 --> 00:20:16,501
( chuckles )

393
00:20:17,837 --> 00:20:19,470
You're not on call, are you?

394
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:22,974
Mitchell's CO got married.

395
00:20:23,009 --> 00:20:26,678
The girl, very young
but very homely.

396
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,763
<i>( elevator bell dings )</i>

397
00:20:28,815 --> 00:20:29,898
Good night.

398
00:20:31,768 --> 00:20:33,768
Don, we should play
squash sometime.

399
00:20:33,820 --> 00:20:36,104
You know, if you have
the energy.

400
00:20:36,156 --> 00:20:38,156
- Sylvia:<i> Arnold!</i>
- Sounds like fun.

401
00:20:40,360 --> 00:20:42,410
<i>( doors close )</i>

402
00:20:42,445 --> 00:20:44,696
How many girls have you
had in this elevator?

403
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:48,283
That's not what that was.

404
00:20:48,335 --> 00:20:50,201
<i>( elevator bell dings )</i>

405
00:20:51,788 --> 00:20:53,504
Elaine:
<i>Hello?</i>

406
00:20:53,540 --> 00:20:55,006
( groans )

407
00:20:55,041 --> 00:20:57,041
I said hello.
You didn't even grunt.

408
00:20:57,093 --> 00:20:59,427
( grunts )

409
00:20:59,462 --> 00:21:02,547
Are you in a creative mood
or a bad mood?

410
00:21:02,599 --> 00:21:05,466
I don't know what I'm doing.

411
00:21:05,518 --> 00:21:07,969
Everything good I have
is from a long time ago.

412
00:21:08,021 --> 00:21:09,938
So what?

413
00:21:09,973 --> 00:21:11,723
You think Picasso
looks at "Guernica"

414
00:21:11,775 --> 00:21:13,641
and says, "Ignore that.
It was a long time ago"?

415
00:21:16,479 --> 00:21:18,446
I got nothing to show her.

416
00:21:18,481 --> 00:21:20,448
Who cares about her?

417
00:21:21,651 --> 00:21:23,901
You should see what she does.

418
00:21:23,903 --> 00:21:27,121
It's so sensual.

419
00:21:29,376 --> 00:21:30,908
Get your camera.

420
00:21:30,961 --> 00:21:32,160
Why?

421
00:21:32,212 --> 00:21:34,629
I want you to take my picture.

422
00:21:34,664 --> 00:21:36,464
No, you don't.

423
00:21:36,499 --> 00:21:37,915
No touching the model.

424
00:21:37,917 --> 00:21:39,417
In here?

425
00:21:39,419 --> 00:21:41,252
I'm not going outside.

426
00:22:01,491 --> 00:22:03,274
You must sit out there
all the time.

427
00:22:05,028 --> 00:22:06,527
I want to see where you live.

428
00:22:13,670 --> 00:22:16,004
How could I be
nervous at this point?

429
00:22:17,340 --> 00:22:18,790
I know.

430
00:22:18,842 --> 00:22:21,959
There's a twinge in my chest.

431
00:22:24,931 --> 00:22:26,464
A pain?

432
00:22:26,516 --> 00:22:29,267
No, it's not that.

433
00:22:29,302 --> 00:22:31,769
I'm positive.

434
00:22:33,556 --> 00:22:35,473
Are you hungry?

435
00:22:35,525 --> 00:22:38,059
Not really.

436
00:22:52,158 --> 00:22:54,459
( phone ringing )

437
00:22:59,582 --> 00:23:01,082
Hello?

438
00:23:05,004 --> 00:23:06,921
Oh, of course.

439
00:23:08,591 --> 00:23:10,174
Yes.

440
00:23:10,176 --> 00:23:12,343
Thank you, Meredith.

441
00:23:15,231 --> 00:23:18,149
Everything okay?

442
00:23:18,184 --> 00:23:19,734
I--

443
00:23:21,438 --> 00:23:22,987
We have to get out of here.

444
00:23:24,691 --> 00:23:27,742
She's coming to take her things
and I don't want to be here.

445
00:23:27,777 --> 00:23:29,744
Oh.

446
00:23:29,779 --> 00:23:31,829
- Okay.
- No, look.

447
00:23:31,865 --> 00:23:33,448
What?

448
00:23:35,835 --> 00:23:40,004
I think if I were you,
this would bother me.

449
00:23:40,039 --> 00:23:43,374
And it shouldn't
because it's almost over.

450
00:23:45,462 --> 00:23:46,928
Good.

451
00:23:54,554 --> 00:23:56,637
I want to see you tonight.

452
00:24:00,393 --> 00:24:02,610
At my place, okay?

453
00:24:03,646 --> 00:24:05,446
Let's go.

454
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:09,033
<i>( elevator bell dings )</i>

455
00:24:12,539 --> 00:24:13,988
Shit.

456
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:15,490
We'll swing by
your place on the way.

457
00:24:15,542 --> 00:24:17,792
- I'll rent.
- You're going to rent pants?

458
00:24:17,827 --> 00:24:20,461
I'll throw my tie over my
shoulder and roll up my sleeves.

459
00:24:20,497 --> 00:24:23,131
- They'll love it.
- Probably will.

460
00:24:27,137 --> 00:24:29,086
_

