that you're renting clubs?

512
00:26:57,227 --> 00:26:59,360
I'll buy a set in the shop.

513
00:27:00,864 --> 00:27:03,314
Megan's moving
her things today.

514
00:27:03,316 --> 00:27:04,949
( sighs )

515
00:27:04,984 --> 00:27:07,118
I didn't know that
was still going on.

516
00:27:10,573 --> 00:27:12,623
They want to punish you.

517
00:27:12,659 --> 00:27:15,376
And then you get mad
and you want to punish them,

518
00:27:15,412 --> 00:27:16,911
but you know it's your fault.

519
00:27:18,214 --> 00:27:20,331
I've been through it before.

520
00:27:20,333 --> 00:27:22,884
Well, how did you handle
client dinners?

521
00:27:22,919 --> 00:27:24,969
I got a date.

522
00:27:25,004 --> 00:27:28,172
I don't have a steady,
so it's too unpredictable.

523
00:27:28,174 --> 00:27:29,674
You don't know how much
they're going to drink

524
00:27:29,676 --> 00:27:31,092
and suddenly
you're with a floozy.

525
00:27:31,144 --> 00:27:33,061
Golf is better.

526
00:27:33,096 --> 00:27:35,179
Jiminy Christmas.

527
00:27:35,181 --> 00:27:37,815
You think you're going to begin
your life over and do it right.

528
00:27:37,851 --> 00:27:39,901
But what if you never get
past the beginning again?

529
00:27:39,936 --> 00:27:42,270
Watch the road.

530
00:27:46,192 --> 00:27:48,659
You filled the whole truck.
That wasn't what we agreed.

531
00:27:48,695 --> 00:27:50,411
I told you
it was gonna be more.

532
00:27:50,447 --> 00:27:52,113
More than double?

533
00:27:52,165 --> 00:27:53,698
Fine, how much you got?

534
00:27:53,700 --> 00:27:56,117
I have $350.

535
00:27:56,169 --> 00:27:58,169
That's enough for me
to leave it on the sidewalk.

536
00:27:58,204 --> 00:28:00,955
That's extortion!

537
00:28:01,007 --> 00:28:03,958
Lady, you are a pain in my ass.

538
00:28:04,010 --> 00:28:06,177
( phone rings )

539
00:28:07,931 --> 00:28:09,547
Donald Draper's office.

540
00:28:09,549 --> 00:28:11,549
I need to speak
with him immediately.

541
00:28:11,601 --> 00:28:13,101
It's Marie Calvet.

542
00:28:13,136 --> 00:28:16,020
Well, I'm sorry, he's not
available right now.

543
00:28:16,055 --> 00:28:17,472
Interrupt him.

544
00:28:17,524 --> 00:28:19,273
I can take a message.

545
00:28:19,309 --> 00:28:21,225
May I say what this
is regarding?

546
00:28:22,529 --> 00:28:24,061
No.

547
00:28:24,063 --> 00:28:25,646
<i>( intercom buzzes )</i>

548
00:28:25,698 --> 00:28:28,533
Caroline: <i>There's a Marie
something on the line.</i>

549
00:28:28,568 --> 00:28:30,201
Marie who?

550
00:28:31,371 --> 00:28:33,321
I got it.
Get off the line.

551
00:28:35,041 --> 00:28:38,292
- <i> Bonjour.</i>
- I am in desperate need of you.

552
00:28:38,328 --> 00:28:40,378
Well, hello to you, too.

553
00:28:40,413 --> 00:28:42,330
I need you to come
to Don's apartment

554
00:28:42,382 --> 00:28:46,134
with $200 and not a penny more!

555
00:28:46,169 --> 00:28:48,169
Calm down.
I'll send someone.

556
00:28:48,221 --> 00:28:51,806
What did I expect? Every time you
get what you want, you run away.

557
00:28:51,841 --> 00:28:53,641
Don't say that.

558
00:28:53,676 --> 00:28:55,593
Bring cash!

559
00:29:00,483 --> 00:29:02,400
- <i> ( knocks )</i>
- It's fine.

560
00:29:02,435 --> 00:29:03,901
[ <i>"A Shallow Sparrow" playing</i> ]

561
00:29:03,937 --> 00:29:05,353
Look where you are.

562
00:29:06,606 --> 00:29:09,490
( clears throat )

563
00:29:09,526 --> 00:29:12,160
Don't.
I'm not ready.

564
00:29:12,195 --> 00:29:14,362
Your subject certainly is.

565
00:29:14,414 --> 00:29:16,914
That's Elaine.
She's...

566
00:29:16,950 --> 00:29:18,950
Overdeveloped?

567
00:29:22,956 --> 00:29:24,705
She's not worthy of you.

568
00:29:26,092 --> 00:29:28,092
You can see it in her eyes.

569
00:29:28,127 --> 00:29:30,378
She doesn't want
to tell you the truth.

570
00:29:34,517 --> 00:29:37,635
Drawing is a much more
rare talent.

571
00:29:37,637 --> 00:29:39,554
Oh.

572
00:29:45,612 --> 00:29:47,478
I expected more.

573
00:30:04,464 --> 00:30:06,163
Holy shit.

574
00:30:06,165 --> 00:30:08,165
- What?
- Where is everything?

575
00:30:08,167 --> 00:30:10,301
- On the truck.
- Pay him.

576
00:30:10,336 --> 00:30:12,837
180 bucks.

577
00:30:15,425 --> 00:30:17,341
My pleasure.

578
00:30:21,347 --> 00:30:22,847
Don agreed to this?

579
00:30:22,899 --> 00:30:25,016
He was very generous.

580
00:30:26,152 --> 00:30:28,352
And you are a true gentleman.

581
00:30:28,404 --> 00:30:30,104
Uh-huh.

582
00:30:30,156 --> 00:30:32,240
Let's get out of here.
I'll buy you a drink.

583
00:30:32,275 --> 00:30:35,826
I hate what he did
to my daughter.

584
00:30:35,862 --> 00:30:37,445
<i>Mon Dieu.</i>
I'm trembling.

585
00:30:39,165 --> 00:30:41,616
You really are.
It's okay.

586
00:30:44,370 --> 00:30:45,703
What are you doing?

587
00:30:45,705 --> 00:30:47,705
( chuckles )

588
00:30:54,180 --> 00:30:55,630
You already emptied
the place out.

589
00:30:55,682 --> 00:30:56,964
You want to defile it as well?

590
00:30:57,016 --> 00:30:58,849
Please.

591
00:30:58,885 --> 00:31:00,801
Take advantage of me.

592
00:31:10,229 --> 00:31:13,197
- You look ravishing.
- Thank you.

593
00:31:13,232 --> 00:31:15,032
I'm really sorry I'm late.

594
00:31:15,068 --> 00:31:16,901
You know that office.

595
00:31:16,903 --> 00:31:18,402
Should we get some wine?

596
00:31:18,454 --> 00:31:20,655
I already did.

597
00:31:20,707 --> 00:31:22,907
I am certainly
picking up the check.

598
00:31:22,909 --> 00:31:24,575
I insist.

599
00:31:24,577 --> 00:31:27,712
It's just you had such good
advice for Miranda and Jill.

600
00:31:27,747 --> 00:31:30,081
Well, they didn't
have agents at all.

601
00:31:30,133 --> 00:31:32,300
My advice was get one.

602
00:31:32,335 --> 00:31:34,302
Well, whatever you did.

603
00:31:34,337 --> 00:31:36,587
To whatever I did.

604
00:31:39,759 --> 00:31:42,176
So, give me the lay.

605
00:31:42,228 --> 00:31:43,678
You know, of the land.

606
00:31:43,730 --> 00:31:45,980
There's not much to tell.

607
00:31:46,015 --> 00:31:48,516
I haven't booked anything
in the last few months.

608
00:31:48,568 --> 00:31:50,434
Not even pilot season?

609
00:31:50,436 --> 00:31:53,237
Well, I turned down
some smaller parts

610
00:31:53,272 --> 00:31:55,690
because Alan thought they'd take
me out of the running for leads.

611
00:31:55,742 --> 00:31:58,159
I'm not in his business,
but I find it hard to believe

612
00:31:58,194 --> 00:32:00,444
that you're losing any contest.

613
00:32:00,446 --> 00:32:02,446
I bet he doesn't know
how to get you in one.

614
00:32:02,498 --> 00:32:05,366
Well, I read
all the time, Harry.

615
00:32:05,418 --> 00:32:06,951
Do you read for lead parts?

616
00:32:07,003 --> 00:32:08,786
Because that's just getting
your name on the right list

617
00:32:08,838 --> 00:32:10,121
with the right
casting director.

618
00:32:10,123 --> 00:32:11,756
Good agents with
real track records

619
00:32:11,791 --> 00:32:13,124
can make that happen.

620
00:32:13,126 --> 00:32:16,594
Alan represents
Angie Dickinson.

621
00:32:16,629 --> 00:32:19,263
You are every man's fantasy.

622
00:32:19,298 --> 00:32:22,299
You're like Ali MacGraw
and Brigitte Bardot had a baby.

623
00:32:22,352 --> 00:32:24,769
You should be the most famous
person in the world right now.

624
00:32:24,804 --> 00:32:27,555
Oh, my goodness.

625
00:32:27,607 --> 00:32:30,057
You should be in this business.

626
00:32:30,109 --> 00:32:33,477
I can't believe
Don threw you away.

627
00:32:36,649 --> 00:32:38,983
He's not a loyal person,
but I am.

628
00:32:40,787 --> 00:32:43,654
You don't think
he could have helped you?

629
00:32:43,706 --> 00:32:46,657
I'm willing to put my money
where my mouth is.

630
00:32:47,877 --> 00:32:50,127
It would be much appreciated.

631
00:32:51,631 --> 00:32:53,547
I'm gonna be honest.
I'm not hungry.

632
00:32:53,583 --> 00:32:55,966
I'd rather get to work
on this immediately.

633
00:32:57,587 --> 00:32:59,754
Well, we can work and eat.
I have a pen.

634
00:32:59,806 --> 00:33:01,972
Well, I have a room upstairs.

635
00:33:03,726 --> 00:33:06,143
It has a phone.
I could make some calls.

636
00:33:08,514 --> 00:33:10,181
Oh, Harry.

637
00:33:12,101 --> 00:33:14,852
I'm not interested.

638
00:33:16,572 --> 00:33:18,823
Megan, you're a big girl.

639
00:33:18,858 --> 00:33:23,194
Maybe you're in this situation because
of how you're reacting to this.

640
00:33:25,364 --> 00:33:26,997
Hold on.
Forget all that.

641
00:33:28,117 --> 00:33:30,034
Come on, have
another glass of wine.

642
00:33:37,543 --> 00:33:39,376
Caroline, I was busy, okay?

643
00:33:39,378 --> 00:33:41,378
Now how about at least
giving me a pat on the back

644
00:33:41,380 --> 00:33:42,963
for remembering
I had a meeting?

645
00:33:43,015 --> 00:33:44,515
Megan:
<i>Hello?</i>

646
00:33:46,352 --> 00:33:48,803
What are you doing here, Megan?

647
00:33:48,855 --> 00:33:50,387
Where the fuck is everything?

648
00:33:50,389 --> 00:33:52,189
Roger...
( gasps )

649
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:56,412
_

650
00:33:56,447 --> 00:33:58,446
He came to help me.

651
00:33:58,481 --> 00:34:01,282
I should go.

652
00:34:01,317 --> 00:34:03,984
Why are you here?
I told you to go to the hotel.

653
00:34:04,036 --> 00:34:07,988
I felt guilty that I left
you here, but obviously...

654
00:34:07,989 --> 00:34:09,650
_

655
00:34:09,651 --> 00:34:11,974
_

656
00:34:14,747 --> 00:34:16,580
I'm late for a meeting.

657
00:34:16,632 --> 00:34:19,834
I guess you don't care that
she's married to my father.

658
00:34:19,886 --> 00:34:21,886
It wasn't my idea.

659
00:34:23,139 --> 00:34:26,090
You don't get to stand
in judgment of me.

660
00:34:30,930 --> 00:34:34,815
<i>( door opens, closes )</i>

661
00:34:34,851 --> 00:34:36,851
<i>( door slams )</i>

662
00:34:40,603 --> 00:34:42,903
Could you give us
a second, honey?

663
00:34:51,447 --> 00:34:53,280
No, thank you.

664
00:34:53,282 --> 00:34:55,082
Have you spoken with Megan?

665
00:34:55,118 --> 00:34:56,700
I just walked in.

666
00:34:56,752 --> 00:34:59,286
Well, I think I should
warn you, we had lunch

667
00:34:59,338 --> 00:35:02,289
and, uh, she's not stable, Don.

668
00:35:02,291 --> 00:35:05,292
She said a lot of crazy things and
I'm sure will continue to say them.

669
00:35:05,294 --> 00:35:08,045
And what will
she say about you?

670
00:35:08,097 --> 00:35:09,346
Crazy things.

671
00:35:09,382 --> 00:35:11,599
All I can say is
she really wants a job.

672
00:35:11,634 --> 00:35:13,217
What does that mean?

673
00:35:13,269 --> 00:35:15,469
Don, come on, nothing happened.

674
00:35:15,471 --> 00:35:17,271
You know she hates me.

675
00:35:18,891 --> 00:35:20,891
You know what?
It's none of my business.

676
00:35:20,943 --> 00:35:23,227
Well, I don't think I could
have helped her anyway.

677
00:35:23,279 --> 00:35:25,146
She quit her soap
and left New York.

678
00:35:25,148 --> 00:35:26,447
That was a really dumb idea.

679
00:35:30,820 --> 00:35:32,403
Pima?

680
00:35:34,157 --> 00:35:36,407
Could you come in?
I have the selects.

681
00:35:39,378 --> 00:35:40,995
Could you get the door?

682
00:35:46,419 --> 00:35:49,970
I put the ones that I like
best on the top row here.

683
00:35:54,310 --> 00:35:57,478
I like this one,
but Stan doesn't.

684
00:35:57,513 --> 00:36:00,181
Stan already
showed these to you?

685
00:36:00,233 --> 00:36:02,233
He was eager to share.

686
00:36:02,268 --> 00:36:04,268
But he knows nothing
about women.

687
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:06,153
What does that mean?

688
00:36:06,189 --> 00:36:08,522
It was just his opinion.

689
00:36:10,576 --> 00:36:13,160
Well, mine's the only
opinion that matters here.

690
00:36:13,196 --> 00:36:15,863
- It's my account.
- Of course, you're in charge.

691
00:36:15,865 --> 00:36:17,581
I know that.

692
00:36:18,868 --> 00:36:20,618
Which one do you like?

693
00:36:22,505 --> 00:36:24,338
I think number three.

694
00:36:24,373 --> 00:36:26,040
Top row.

695
00:36:30,763 --> 00:36:32,713
You've never been married.

696
00:36:33,933 --> 00:36:36,217
Nope.

697
00:36:36,219 --> 00:36:38,719
Me either.

698
00:36:38,771 --> 00:36:41,305
The adventures
I would have missed.

699
00:36:42,558 --> 00:36:44,225
Number four.

700
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:49,563
I would love
to take your picture.

701
00:36:49,565 --> 00:36:52,233
Well, I'm--

702
00:36:52,235 --> 00:36:54,118
I don't know about that.

703
00:36:55,738 --> 00:36:58,405
The way you're looking
at me right now...

704
00:37:03,879 --> 00:37:05,913
I would capture that.

705
00:37:25,768 --> 00:37:27,651
How are you?

706
00:37:30,156 --> 00:37:32,606
Where is he?
He was right behind me.

707
00:37:37,580 --> 00:37:39,530
I don't want anything of yours.

708
00:37:48,424 --> 00:37:50,624
I wasn't going to say a word.

709
00:37:50,626 --> 00:37:52,626
I wasn't going to give you
the satisfaction

710
00:37:52,628 --> 00:37:54,962
of knowing that
you ruined my life.

711
00:37:56,132 --> 00:37:57,514
Megan.

712
00:37:57,550 --> 00:38:00,100
Why did I believe you?

713
00:38:01,437 --> 00:38:05,306
Why did I believe
the things you said to me?

714
00:38:05,308 --> 00:38:07,891
Why am I being punished
for being young?

715
00:38:09,445 --> 00:38:12,980
I gave up everything for you
because I believed you.

716
00:38:13,032 --> 00:38:14,815
And you're nothing but a liar.

717
00:38:17,620 --> 00:38:22,072
An aging, sloppy, selfish liar.

718
00:38:35,004 --> 00:38:36,670
You're right.

719
00:38:36,672 --> 00:38:39,173
You're gonna write me a check?

720
00:38:39,175 --> 00:38:42,810
I want you to have

721
00:38:42,845 --> 00:38:45,312
the life you deserve.

722
00:38:51,354 --> 00:38:53,153
( scoffs )

723
00:38:53,189 --> 00:38:54,855
Are you kidding me?

724
00:38:54,907 --> 00:38:56,990
No.

725
00:38:57,026 --> 00:38:59,193
A million dollars?

726
00:38:59,195 --> 00:39:01,445
Why are you doing this to me?
It's not funny.

727
00:39:01,497 --> 00:39:04,198
I don't want to fight anymore.

728
00:39:04,200 --> 00:39:06,750
Well, I know it's not real.

729
00:39:06,786 --> 00:39:08,419
Nothing about you is.

730
00:39:08,454 --> 00:39:11,622
It is real.
Please take it.

731
00:39:37,483 --> 00:39:39,316
Megan, I'm sorry.

732
00:39:40,486 --> 00:39:42,236
Send me the papers.

733
00:39:47,743 --> 00:39:49,626
I want you to be honest.

734
00:39:49,662 --> 00:39:51,628
Should I let my hair grow out?

735
00:39:51,664 --> 00:39:53,130
Good night, everybody.

736
00:39:53,165 --> 00:39:55,999
Ed, you were right.
Pima's a treasure.

737
00:39:56,051 --> 00:39:57,835
Is she?

738
00:39:57,887 --> 00:40:00,254
You don't like the work?
Because I was thinking,

739
00:40:00,306 --> 00:40:02,756
you know, she'd be right
for Butler Shoes.

740
00:40:02,758 --> 00:40:04,808
Or maybe Topaz Pantyhose.

741
00:40:04,844 --> 00:40:06,560
She's got a thing for legs.

742
00:40:06,595 --> 00:40:08,395
Women's legs.

743
00:40:08,431 --> 00:40:10,230
Sorry to disappoint you.

744
00:40:10,266 --> 00:40:13,400
I'm not disappointed.

745
00:40:13,436 --> 00:40:16,019
Neither was she.

746
00:40:18,941 --> 00:40:20,574
Really?

747
00:40:20,609 --> 00:40:22,276
Does that bother you?

748
00:40:24,613 --> 00:40:26,163
No.

749
00:40:26,198 --> 00:40:27,998
But I bet it might
bother Ellen.

750
00:40:28,033 --> 00:40:29,283
Elaine.

751
00:40:29,285 --> 00:40:31,034
This is none of your business.

752
00:40:31,086 --> 00:40:33,620
No.

753
00:40:33,622 --> 00:40:35,622
It's Pima's business,

754
00:40:35,674 --> 00:40:38,926
which turns out to be
more advertising than art.

755
00:40:40,546 --> 00:40:41,795
She's a hustler.

756
00:40:41,797 --> 00:40:44,131
You're jealous.

757
00:40:44,183 --> 00:40:46,216
She tried
the same thing with me.

758
00:40:46,268 --> 00:40:48,469
But she didn't get as far.

759
00:40:48,471 --> 00:40:51,355
And that's why I'm not going
to give her another job.

760
00:40:53,058 --> 00:40:54,892
I don't believe you.

761
00:40:54,944 --> 00:40:57,561
Which part?

762
00:41:08,961 --> 00:41:10,594
<i>( door closes )</i>

763
00:41:12,231 --> 00:41:13,677
_

764
00:41:15,702 --> 00:41:17,456
_

765
00:41:17,457 --> 00:41:19,347
_

766
00:41:19,348 --> 00:41:22,101
_

767
00:41:22,975 --> 00:41:24,475
Not particularly.

768
00:41:24,476 --> 00:41:28,295
_

769
00:41:28,296 --> 00:41:31,116
_

770
00:41:31,951 --> 00:41:34,785
So you ordered room service?

771
00:41:34,786 --> 00:41:37,508
_

772
00:41:37,509 --> 00:41:40,267
_

773
00:41:40,876 --> 00:41:42,159
I don't care.

774
00:41:42,211 --> 00:41:44,411
She's leaving Papa.

775
00:41:46,832 --> 00:41:48,132
I'm going to pack.

776
00:41:48,133 --> 00:41:50,606
_

777
00:41:51,514 --> 00:41:53,876
_

778
00:41:55,224 --> 00:41:57,007
I don't want to hear about it.

779
00:41:57,698 --> 00:41:59,918
_

780
00:42:00,595 --> 00:42:03,989
_

781
00:42:04,316 --> 00:42:06,016
You know it's a sin
to be a ghoul

782
00:42:06,068 --> 00:42:07,684
and feed on everyone's pain?

783
00:42:09,155 --> 00:42:13,323
She's been very unhappy
for a very long time.

784
00:42:13,359 --> 00:42:15,359
At least she did
something about it.

785
00:42:22,084 --> 00:42:24,001
( sighs )

786
00:42:24,036 --> 00:42:26,036
I'm exhausted.

787
00:42:26,088 --> 00:42:29,339
Me, too.

788
00:42:29,375 --> 00:42:31,425
Did you print anything?

789
00:42:31,460 --> 00:42:33,210
They're drying.

790
00:42:33,212 --> 00:42:35,262
You did?

791
00:42:35,297 --> 00:42:37,714
How were they?
What did Pima say?

792
00:42:40,886 --> 00:42:42,719
She loved them.

793
00:42:42,721 --> 00:42:44,688
How about you?

794
00:42:52,064 --> 00:42:54,615
<i>( siren blaring )</i>

795
00:43:12,218 --> 00:43:15,135
Do you want a drink?
I just have vodka.

796
00:43:15,171 --> 00:43:17,421
Yes, please.

797
00:43:17,423 --> 00:43:20,557
Oh, I got you something.

798
00:43:20,593 --> 00:43:22,259
Open it.

799
00:43:27,149 --> 00:43:29,099
It's a New York City guidebook.

800
00:43:29,151 --> 00:43:31,101
Finally start your tour.

801
00:43:32,354 --> 00:43:33,654
Go on.

802
00:43:36,525 --> 00:43:39,109
Can't you see
I don't want anything?

803
00:43:42,698 --> 00:43:45,249
Look, I'm pretty sure
I had a worse day than you.

804
00:43:45,284 --> 00:43:46,750
Please don't be in a mood.

805
00:43:46,785 --> 00:43:49,036
I'm not in a mood.

806
00:43:49,088 --> 00:43:51,622
And you've never had
a worse day than me.

807
00:43:51,624 --> 00:43:54,208
You don't think
I've felt grief?

808
00:43:54,260 --> 00:43:56,793
You knew that about me
the first night we met.

809
00:43:59,849 --> 00:44:02,683
I've been trying
to talk myself out of it.

810
00:44:02,718 --> 00:44:04,468
Don't.

811
00:44:04,470 --> 00:44:05,969
No.

812
00:44:06,021 --> 00:44:08,355
Talk myself out
of what I have to say.

813
00:44:08,390 --> 00:44:10,858
You're scared.
I understand.

814
00:44:12,311 --> 00:44:15,028
But I took care
of everything today.

815
00:44:16,649 --> 00:44:18,949
I've been separated
a long time.

816
00:44:21,153 --> 00:44:24,905
You're not the first
thing to come along.

817
00:44:26,625 --> 00:44:28,325
I'm ready.

818
00:44:28,377 --> 00:44:30,160
( scoffs )

819
00:44:30,162 --> 00:44:32,963
You're fooling yourself
if you think this'll make a difference.

820
00:44:32,998 --> 00:44:34,831
You don't think I know
what's going on here?

821
00:44:34,833 --> 00:44:37,084
Look at this dump.

822
00:44:37,136 --> 00:44:39,303
I know you think
you deserve this.

823
00:44:39,338 --> 00:44:40,754
I've done it.

824
00:44:43,475 --> 00:44:45,475
I left my daughter.

825
00:44:45,511 --> 00:44:48,228
Stop blaming yourself.

826
00:44:48,264 --> 00:44:50,814
No.

827
00:44:50,849 --> 00:44:53,400
I had two children.

828
00:44:53,435 --> 00:44:55,018
Two girls.

829
00:44:56,939 --> 00:44:59,356
One died and one...

830
00:45:03,245 --> 00:45:06,747
my oldest is in Racine
with her father.

831
00:45:10,035 --> 00:45:12,536
Why? Don't you want
to ask why?

832
00:45:14,673 --> 00:45:16,173
No.

833
00:45:23,799 --> 00:45:26,383
I told you about my heart.

834
00:45:28,053 --> 00:45:30,554
I don't want to feel
anything else.

835
00:45:32,191 --> 00:45:35,025
When I was with you,
I forgot about...

836
00:45:39,031 --> 00:45:40,731
her.

837
00:45:42,117 --> 00:45:43,817
I don't ever want to do that.

838
